---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="FAQ">
  <!-- Hero Section - In white card -->
  <section class="bg-gray-100">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 pt-16 pb-12 max-w-4xl">
      <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 shadow-lg">
        <div class="inline-block mb-4">
          <div class="h-1 w-20 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-600 to-blue-400 rounded-full mb-6"></div>
        </div>
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-6 text-gray-900">Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
          Common questions about Knowledge That Compounds and our consulting services.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ Section - Seamless -->
  <section class="bg-gray-100 pb-16">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl">
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <!-- Question 1 -->
        <details class="group bg-white border-2 border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6 cursor-pointer hover:border-blue-400 transition-all shadow-sm hover:shadow-lg">
          <summary class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between">
            <span>What is Knowledge That Compounds (KTC)?</span>
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-blue-600 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
            </svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="mt-4 pt-4 border-t border-gray-200 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <p class="mb-3">
              KTC is a methodology for building AI systems with persistent memory. Instead of every conversation 
              starting from zero, knowledge accumulates and compounds over time through specialized "Brains."
            </p>
            <p>
              Think of it as creating a team of AI assistants that remember everything, share knowledge 
              intelligently, and improve with every interaction.
            </p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <!-- Question 2 -->
        <details class="group bg-white border-2 border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6 cursor-pointer hover:border-blue-400 transition-all shadow-sm hover:shadow-lg">
          <summary class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between">
            <span>How is this different from just using ChatGPT?</span>
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-blue-600 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
            </svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="mt-4 pt-4 border-t border-gray-200 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <p class="mb-3">
              Standard AI tools like ChatGPT have no persistent memory. Every conversation starts fresh, 
              context disappears between sessions, and you constantly repeat yourself.
            </p>
            <p>
              KTC builds systems where knowledge persists, accumulates, and routes to the right Brain. 
              It's the difference between having a brilliant colleague with amnesia versus one with perfect memory.
            </p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <!-- Question 3 -->
        <details class="group bg-white border-2 border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6 cursor-pointer hover:border-blue-400 transition-all shadow-sm hover:shadow-lg">
          <summary class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between">
            <span>What is a "Brain" in the KTC system?</span>
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-blue-600 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
            </svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="mt-4 pt-4 border-t border-gray-200 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <p class="mb-3">
              A Brain is a specialized AI assistant with persistent memory for a specific domain. For example:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 ml-4 text-gray-700">
              <li>Marketing Brain: Remembers campaign strategies, brand voice, past results</li>
              <li>Research Brain: Accumulates findings, sources, insights over time</li>
              <li>Operations Brain: Tracks processes, decisions, team workflows</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-3">
              Each Brain maintains context, learns from interactions, and shares knowledge with other Brains when needed.
            </p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <!-- Question 4 -->
        <details class="group bg-white border-2 border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6 cursor-pointer hover:border-blue-400 transition-all shadow-sm hover:shadow-lg">
          <summary class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between">
            <span>How long does implementation take?</span>
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-blue-600 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
            </svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="mt-4 pt-4 border-t border-gray-200 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <p class="mb-3">
              It depends on the tier:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 ml-4 text-gray-700">
              <li><strong>Starter:</strong> You implement yourself with our templates (1-2 weeks)</li>
              <li><strong>Professional:</strong> We architect and train your team (2-4 weeks)</li>
              <li><strong>Enterprise:</strong> Full implementation with all standards (4-8 weeks)</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-3">
              The system improves continuously after launch as knowledge compounds.
            </p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <!-- Question 5 -->
        <details class="group bg-white border-2 border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6 cursor-pointer hover:border-blue-400 transition-all shadow-sm hover:shadow-lg">
          <summary class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between">
            <span>Do I need technical skills to use KTC?</span>
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-blue-600 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
            </svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="mt-4 pt-4 border-t border-gray-200 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <p class="mb-3">
              No. KTC is designed for knowledge workers, not developers.
            </p>
            <p>
              You interact with Brains through natural conversation. The methodology focuses on how to 
              structure knowledge, not on coding. If you can use ChatGPT, you can use KTC.
            </p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <!-- Question 6 -->
        <details class="group bg-white border-2 border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6 cursor-pointer hover:border-blue-400 transition-all shadow-sm hover:shadow-lg">
          <summary class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between">
            <span>What kind of results can I expect?</span>
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-blue-600 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
            </svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="mt-4 pt-4 border-t border-gray-200 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <p class="mb-3">
              Organizations using KTC report:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 ml-4 text-gray-700">
              <li>Faster decision-making (context already captured)</li>
              <li>Reduced repetitive work (Brains remember processes)</li>
              <li>Better knowledge retention (nothing gets lost between sessions)</li>
              <li>Improved team collaboration (shared knowledge across Brains)</li>
              <li>Compounding returns (system gets smarter over time)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </details>

        <!-- Question 7 -->
        <details class="group bg-white border-2 border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6 cursor-pointer hover:border-blue-400 transition-all shadow-sm hover:shadow-lg">
          <summary class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between">
            <span>Is my data secure?</span>
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-blue-600 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
            </svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="mt-4 pt-4 border-t border-gray-200 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <p class="mb-3">
              Yes. KTC systems use enterprise-grade AI platforms (like Claude by Anthropic) with strong 
              privacy and security measures.
            </p>
            <p>
              Your Brains and their knowledge are private to your organization. We teach methodology 
              and help you implement—you own and control all data.
            </p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <!-- Question 8 -->
        <details class="group bg-white border-2 border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6 cursor-pointer hover:border-blue-400 transition-all shadow-sm hover:shadow-lg">
          <summary class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between">
            <span>What's the difference between the consulting tiers?</span>
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-blue-600 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
            </svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="mt-4 pt-4 border-t border-gray-200 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <p class="mb-3">
              <strong>Starter ($500+):</strong> Best for individuals or small teams who want to 
              implement 1-2 Brains themselves. Includes templates and guidance.
            </p>
            <p class="mb-3">
              <strong>Professional ($5,000+):</strong> Best for teams and departments. We architect 
              your Brain network and train your team. Includes 2-3 Brains and implementation support.
            </p>
            <p>
              <strong>Enterprise ($50,000+):</strong> Best for organizations implementing company-wide. 
              Full Standards 1-14, done-for-you implementation, self-improving systems, ongoing support.
            </p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <!-- Question 9 -->
        <details class="group bg-white border-2 border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6 cursor-pointer hover:border-blue-400 transition-all shadow-sm hover:shadow-lg">
          <summary class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between">
            <span>Can KTC work for my industry?</span>
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-blue-600 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
            </svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="mt-4 pt-4 border-t border-gray-200 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <p class="mb-3">
              Yes. KTC is methodology-agnostic and works across industries:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 ml-4 text-gray-700">
              <li>Consulting firms (capture client context, proposals, insights)</li>
              <li>Research teams (accumulate findings, literature, hypotheses)</li>
              <li>Marketing agencies (brand voice, campaigns, performance data)</li>
              <li>Legal practices (case precedents, client history, research)</li>
              <li>Product teams (feature decisions, user research, roadmaps)</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-3">
              Any knowledge work where context and memory matter benefits from KTC.
            </p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <!-- Question 10 -->
        <details class="group bg-white border-2 border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6 cursor-pointer hover:border-blue-400 transition-all shadow-sm hover:shadow-lg">
          <summary class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between">
            <span>How do I get started?</span>
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-blue-600 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
            </svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="mt-4 pt-4 border-t border-gray-200 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <p class="mb-3">
              Start with a discovery call:
            </p>
            <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 ml-4 text-gray-700">
              <li>Schedule a discovery call via our contact page</li>
              <li>We discuss your needs and recommend the right tier</li>
              <li>You receive a detailed proposal with timeline and pricing</li>
              <li>We begin implementation once you approve</li>
            </ol>
            <p class="mt-3">
              <a href="/contact" class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-700 underline font-semibold">
                Contact us to schedule your discovery call →
              </a>
            </p>
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>

      <!-- CTA Section -->
      <div class="mt-16 pt-8 text-center">
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6 font-semibold">
          Still have questions?
        </p>
        <a href="/contact" class="inline-block bg-blue-600 text-white px-10 py-4 rounded-lg hover:bg-blue-700 font-semibold text-lg shadow-xl hover:shadow-2xl transition-all hover:-translate-y-1">
          Get In Touch
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>